# Part A: System Documentation
## Software Development

## Requirements Definition

### Aim
The aim of this project is to create an educational website that shows learning content in a
simple and intereactive way. The website should respond quickly when users click or type and
give clear instructions.

## Functional Requirements

- The website must have an interactive design.
- Users must be able to choose and switch between different learning modules.
- The system must accept user input and check if it is correct.
- The website must update straight away without refreshing the page 
- The systen must use data structure like dictionaries etc.


## Non-Functional Requirements

- The website must respond within 100 milliseconds os it feels fast.
- All content must be reachabe within three clicks from the main page.
- The website must work properly on computers and mobile devices.
- The system must keep data secure using proper encryption.


## Constraints

- Only free and open-source tools can be used.
- The website must be built using HTML
- The project must be finished by Term 2, Week 2

# User Specifications

## Target Users
The main users are students who want access learning content online.

## What Users Should Be Able To Do

- Select different learning modules
- Move easily between sections
- Type answers or enter information
- Receive instand feedback
- See their progress

## User Expectations
- the website should be easy to understand.
- it should load quickly.
- Navigation should be simple and not confusing
- The design shoud be neat and clear


## Purpose

The purpose of this website is to provide studets with online learning content in a simple
and interactive way. It is designed to help students move through lessons, answer questions,
and get feedback straight away. The system makes learning more engaging and easier to
access.


## Design Decisions

- HTML were used to create the layout and design.
- State-based navigation was used so users can switch between modules without reloading
 the page.
- Responsive design was used so the website works on computers and mobile phones.

## Functionality

- Users can choose a learning module from the main menu.
- The selected content appears instantly.
- users can enter answers and the system checks if they are correct.
- Feedback is shown immediately
- The website updates automatically without refreshing.
- Lesson content and progress are stored using internal data structures.






